  "date": "2026-04-11",
  "poem": {
    "content": "Sun bleeds through the library pane,\ndust motes dancing in a golden rain.\nRegret, a vacuum in my chest,\na toy horse broken, put to rest.\n\nThe stairs ascend, a daunting height,\na prize awaits, bathed in pale light,\nbut I gather only shadows there,\na few bright hopes, thin as air.\n\nThe entire world feels out of sync,\na lesson learned, a bitter drink.\nThe impact of choices, sharp and deep,\na secret promise I couldn't keep.\n\nA gap between what is and seems,\na trick of fate, disrupting dreams.\nThe horse now gone, its silent plea,\nleaves only emptiness mocking me.",
